    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="698"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d698">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">War Trade Board Files: Shipping and Tonnage,
                    Switzerland, Vol. II</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the War Trade Board</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MVC1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McCormick</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the French Deputy High Commissioner</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DBE1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">De Billy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 11, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Sir</hi>: I have your letter of November 5,
                    relative to the possible acquisition by Switzerland of enemy ships in neutral
                    ports, particularly Spain. You state that your Government is advising the Swiss
                    Legation that it can not at this time consider any arrangement whereby ships
                    under enemy flag may be transferred to neutrals. The views of the War Trade
                    Board, an expression of which <pb facs="0824" n="1658" xml:id="pg_1658"/> you
                    request, are that it would be unwise at this time to consent to any such
                    transfer as is proposed.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MVC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vance McCormick</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
